BrightSource Seeks Permit for 750-Megawatt Solar-Thermal Project

-- B y   E h r e n   G o o s s e n s
-- 
2011-10-14T17:49:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-14/brightsource-seeks-permit-for-750-megawatt-solar-thermal-project.html
BrightSource Energy Inc., a
developer of solar-thermal power plants, is seeking permission
to build a 750-megawatt project in  Southern California .  BrightSource filed an application for certification with
the  California Energy Commission  for its Rio Mesa project in
Riverside County, the Oakland, California-based company said
today in a statement. The project with have three, 250-megawatt
plants that use mirrors to focus sunlight on a boiler, producing
steam to drive a turbine.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ehren Goossens in New York at 
 egoossens1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Wade at 
 wwade4@bloomberg.net  